        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to perform polarization observation at Band 7. 
There is only one choice for the correlator setup.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to use C36-1 and C36-6 two array configurations to measure the dust polarization 
at the scale of  1"~5.3" and 0.1"~1.4". The data probe the scales within the 1/3 of primary beam and also achieve high angular resolution of ~0.1" at Band 7 with 6 hr of observing time (3 hr in each configuration).</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Because each configuration requires at least 3hr observations and our source IRAS 4A is a bright source, we can acheive very high sensitivity in each configuration. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
